// NewGatewayDisk.cm, Murray February 16, 1981  6:00 PM// First get/build a clean empty disk.// I suggest that you start by ERASEing and Installing a NewOS.// I suggest that you get listings of//    [Maxc]<AltoDocs>NetTopology.press,//    [Ivy]<Portola>Pup-Network.txt, and//    [Ivy]<Portola>Mesa6>Gateway.signals.FTP Iris ^  Directory/c Mesa ^    Retrieve/c RunMesa.Run!1 ^    Retrieve/s MesaFont.strike SysFont.strike ^  Close/c ^  Open IVY ^  Directory/c Portola>Mesa6 ^    Retrieve/c Gateway.image ^    Retrieve/c MesaGateCPChain.br MesaGateEIAChain.br ^    Retrieve/c NewGateway.txt NewGateway-user.cm ^  Close/c ^  Open MAXC ^    Retrieve/c <BootFiles>DMT.boot ^    Retrieve/c <Alto>InstallSwat.run ^    Retrieve/c <Alto>SYS.ERRORS ^InstallSwatDelete InstallSwat.run// Copy/Edit User.cm _ NewGateway-user.cm// Delete NewGateway-user.cm// Rename <HostName>.txt _ NewGateway.txt// Edit <HostName>.txt to//   1) include your IO devices//   2) load the microcode (delete the other microcode file), and//   3) supply the appropiate ZONE and CORRECTION for the TimeServer.// You may want to add or delete a few files from the boot list// because the disk will be very full.